HEADWORD: Deterration
<hw>De`ter*ra"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>de</ets> + <ets>terra</ets> earth: cf. F.
<ets>d⟦eacute⟧terrer</ets> to unearth.]</ety> <def>The uncovering of
anything buried or covered with earth; a taking out of the earth or
ground.</def> <rj><au>Woodward.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

